.SH "NAME"
odgi_position \- position parts of the graph as defined by query criteria
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBodgi position\fP [\fB\-i, \-\-target\fP=\fIFILE\fP] [\fIOPTION\fP]...
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The odgi position(1) command position parts of the graph as defined by query criteria.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Graph Files IO"
.sp
\fB\-i, \-\-target\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Describe positions in this graph.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-x, \-\-source\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
  Translate positions from this graph into the target graph using common \f(CR\-\-lift\-paths\fP shared between both graphs [default: use the same source/target
graph]
.RE
.SS "Position Options"
.sp
\fB\-r, \-\-ref\-paths\fP=\fISTRING\fP
.RS 4
Translate the given positions into positions relative to this reference path.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-R, \-\-ref\-paths\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Use the ref\-paths in FILE.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-l, \-\-lift\-path\fP=\fISTRING\fP
.RS 4
  Lift positions from \f(CR\-\-source\fP to \f(CR\-\-target\fP via coordinates in this path common to both graphs [default: all common paths
between \f(CR\-\-source\fP and \f(CR\-\-target\fP].
.RE
.sp
\fB\-g, \-\-graph\-pos\fP=\fI[[node_id]\fB]\fP]\fP
.RS 4
A graph position, e.g. 42,10,+ or 302,0,\-.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-F, \-\-path\-pos\-file\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
A file with one path position per line.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-b, \-\-bed\-input\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
A BED file of ranges in paths in the graph to lift into the target graph \f(CR\-v\fP, \f(CR\-\-give\-graph\-pos\fP emit graph positions.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-v, \-\-give\-graph\-pos\fP
.RS 4
Emit graph positions (node,offset,strand) rather than path positions.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-d, \-\-search\-radius\fP=\fISTRING\fP
.RS 4
Limit coordinate conversion breadth\-first search up to DISTANCE bp from each given position [default: 10000].
.RE
.SS "Threading"
.sp
\fB\-t, \-\-threads\fP=\fIN\fP
.RS 4
Number of threads to use.
.RE
.SS "Program Information"
.sp
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Print a help message for \fBodgi position\fP.
.RE
